cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper proposes a deep neural network model for reconstructing HDR images from LDR images, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) techniques. The model is based on convolutional neural networks (cs.MM) and uses a chaining structure to infer the relationship between LDR images with different exposures and illumination (cs.LG). Finally, the model aims to restore the light information of the actual physical world, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques.
